Two of my Bugatti work in progress that has been stalled for a while (along with the Shelby cobra 2022) as I’ve been very busy getting contacts and commission work done. I should be getting back to these next week while focusing on finishing work this week and the coming weekend. 

One of them is the Bugatti Rafale in its very early stage, and will probably let undergo quite some change throughout the process. 
The other one is a much older one that I’ve been working on. No name yet lol. 

See ya ✌🏼

node.text:
Alright, hear me out guys -
Break the rules. Design things out of the ordinary. Create your own rules, and directions. Bend them. Break them. Go nuts.

In this case, a design that is not based on anything at all other than a random sketch in my sketchbook. Inspired by so many other things, not just cars, but might see a lot of different inspiration from other cars and brands here. What I had in mind is simply designing a BMW and not following any BMW design DNA/language at all. And I like it - both the result, and the freedom. 

A BMW that you (obviously) didn’t expect to see. Some modern, retro. Futuristic touches overall and voila: 

BMW _ zero one
